14. Interview Questions Related to Push
What does push() do?
What is the time complexity of push()?
Why is push() an O(1) operation?
What happens during Stack Overflow?
How is push() implemented using an array?
How is push() implemented using a linked list?
15. One Analogy to Remember Everything

Imagine you're stacking books.

Initially

Top
 ↓
Java
Python

Now you buy a new book:

DSA

Where do you place it?

Top
 ↓
DSA
Java
Python

You always place the new book on the top.

That is PUSH.

You never insert it in the middle or at the bottom.

⭐ Quick Revision (30 Seconds)
Push = Insert a new element at the Top of the stack.
Every new element becomes the new Top.
Follows LIFO (Last In, First Out).
push() returns the inserted element (though we usually ignore the return value).
Time Complexity = O(1).
Array implementation can cause Stack Overflow if full.
Linked List implementation inserts the new node at the head (Top).

Memory Trick:
PUSH = Put on the Top 
Think of adding a new plate or a new book—you always place it on top, never in the middle or bottom.
